If you are a chai lover, then ask for their masala tea/ masala chai it wouldnt disappoint. Definitely recommend. Street parking nearby, street corner style place located in the heart of river north in downtown. Posting few pictures from my recent visit, check it out!

After eating here twice, I'm confident in my 5 star rating of Moti Cafe. I love the flavors and variety of dishes they have! It's unique and is something I didn't realize I was missing in my life.  The first time I got the paneer tikka rice bowl through delivery and loved it. Went back for dine-in using a Groupon and got almost the same rice bowl, the samosa pav, and naan flatbread. The paneer tikka rice bowl is fantastic. The masala corn wasn't very flavorful so next time I'd just get a more crunchy topping instead. The naan flatbread I got was very similar to the rice bowl just in pizza form. Next time, would just order either the rice bowl or the flatbread instead of both. As for the samosa pav, the samosa filling was well flavored but the outside wasn't very crunchy. Overall, everything I've had on the menu so far has been pretty solid and the portion sizes are hearty. I look forward to going back to try more!  As for non-food aspects of the experience: The food was prepared quickly and the staff was very friendly. They have 3 tables for outdoor seating, hand sanitizer available, and water available upon request. Saw them wearing gloves in the restaurant and cleaning the table and chairs between guests.
Food was so tasty. Certainly worth a return visit. Prices that won't shock you.
Loved on street seating. Best vada Paav, naan Bites and samosa paav I ever had. Try it. ☺️
This place is great! Walked by so many times without atopping, but have eaten lunch here 3 days in a row. Real good!

The food here was pretty good, but not astonishing. I got Tikka masala, yellow rice, and some Momo dumplings. Cashier/waitress was very nice. They had outdoor seating but it didn't look like they had indoor seating. My only problem was that my fanta soda was not very cold and was one of warm, even though I got it from a refrigerator.

Ordered delivery and the food was delicious, well packed, and great value! I had the flatbread with paneer, a samosa chaat, and a paneer tikka wrap and all three were delicious! Be mindful if you can't tolerate a high level of spice, make sure you specify that, because this food was as authentic and tasty as the motherland herself (so yes, has spice)!

I have tried both the chicken tikka masala and the chicken biryani. The tikki masala did not taste authentic - instead it tasted like 50% tikki masala, 50% creamy tomato soup, and no rice was provided. The chicken biryani  had very fragrant spices with strong notes of clover, I usually love biryani but the clover on this dish was just too much. Both dishes contained about one chicken breast quartered into 4 large chunks. There are other Indian spots in the neighborhood that have their menu mastered, I'll stick to those spots.
Friendly, great food. Order ahead and pick up  the bums outside’ll swap u. Unfortunate for a great place.

I’ve been meaning to stop in here for awhile, but didn’t get to it and then when COVID hit, I decided to just order delivery because I couldn’t wait any longer. Plus, I wanted to give small businesses my support.  I ordered delivery from Moti Cafe today and it was amazing! I ordered the MOMOS (steamed dumplings) and they came steaming with the sauces on the side. The Sweet Chili sauce wasn’t over spiced and the lava sauce had a perfect kick to it. I also ordered the Vada Pav and it was delicious. The bun was soft and the potato patty was very filling for just one order. It was pretty spicy so if you don’t like spice, I wouldn’t recommend it. I ordered their “Moti” sauce on the side and it was probably one of the best sauces I’ve had in awhile. It was creamy like an aioli and was SPICY. If I could buy it in a bottle I would.  I would definitely order from here again, it’s a small business so do definitely give them your business!l

This is the best Indian restaurant in downtown Chicago! Loved the atmosphere and friendly staff. The owner was welcoming and I loved the food. I’ve tried chicken tikka wrap, it was delicious and authentic Indian flavor. I’m looking forward to try more dishes!!

Moti has the sauce, and they definitely are not lost in it. We tried just about every taco they had, and if you are into spicy, hearty, sweet, or light there is something for you at Moti. We chased our spicy tika tacos (if your favorite taco at Velvet Taco is the tika taco you HAVE to try Moti) and loaded fries with delicious Moti mini pancakes loaded with nutella and strawberries. This is the perfect quick lunch or dinner in River North, or great desert stop after a more upscale dinner in the neighborhood. Everyone needs to go see Jay & Rushi,

If you are looking for quick Indian street food, well indo-american or indo-fusion street food, definitely check this place out. I ordered a paneer Tikka flat bread and chilli garlic veg momos. The flat bread didn't seem to have fresh paneer but frozen/reheated and it become a mess with all the sauces, and momos were also reheated, so the flour wrap became a bit chewy after a while. Overall, it's good for satiating a craving but it can be done better. Both items were decent if u like spicy. For me it was a tad too much and I had to eat it three times, and finish along with some sweet cold drink.. it's right at the intersection and I believe there are delivery options. The interiors are simple and you can also get some nice Indian drinks there. The price maybe a bit higher than expected but definitely worth a trip if you are in downtown Chicago.

I don't think I have ever left a 2 star review on Google, but I guess there's a first time for everything. I will start by saying the place is new and the staff was super friendly, so we'll consider coming back and I'll update the review if the experience is better.  The food was cold, I mean literally the meat was cold, the rice was cold, all the toppings were cold. Then, as far as Indian food goes, it didn't really have that authentic Indian flavor we were seeking. The rice was just normal rice and all the toppings are just very small toppings with no added flavor or anything to them. I was expecting the toppings to be actual vegetables, whole cut, not just a topping.  Essentially I ate a bowl with regular rice, dry chicken with some decent flavor, then a bunch of tiny little cut up veggies (truly a topping) and some Indian sauce.  I hope this place does well, but I think they might need to change it up a bit.

Staff were friendly and helpful. I was at a loss where to start, and the suggestions and descriptions the staff gave really helped me figure out what I wanted. I have never in my life liked matcha before today, but the matcha lemonade is to die for. So good!

So we walked in and immediately got a good vibe. I ordered a mango bubble tea and some Indian moti cakes. But they told me they had a menu change and didn’t sell bubble tea and instead did smoothies :( I was kind of sad but I ended up getting a matcha lemonade. When I got it I was immediately surprised because it was green! But overall, the taste was okay, but left kind of a sour aftertaste in your mouth. Plus, the green makes it kind of unappetizing. But it is a super cute little cafe and right across the street from the Felix hotel. They have teas, and wraps, and a bunch of cute little Indian street foods.  They gave us a sample of a Indian tea/coffee drink and it was boiling hot. But it tasted good, so that’s a plus. We got our food about 10 minutes after we ordered it and matcha cakes are like little pancakes. You can pick any topping you want, though. They are superrrrrr cute! And they taste amazing. Definitely would recommend them. Their cups are super cute and the Moti makes cake in like a cardboard bowl. They are super cute and are dressed really nicely. They have little flags poked into them and they are super enjoyable.

I had the paneer tikka wrap, my husband had the chicken tikka wrap and we got moti fries to share. The portions were perfect, flavors were perfect. My family and I visited Moti Cafe on Memorial Day in the afternoon for a light lunch/snack. We were so impressed with this new restaurant in River North!  We tried a number of things from the menu: Matcha Lemonade: SO good! I love matcha lemonade in the summer, and Moti Cafe did a great job balancing the matcha and lemonade, it wasn't too bitter or too sweet, both flavors came through.  Berry Smoothie: Very refreshing, especially with the...  FRIES! : Wow they were great! My brother proclaimed that they were better than Portillo's (high praise in our family). The fries themselves were crispy and the sauce was so unique and tasty. There was definitely some heat, but nothing unmanageable and a great take on French fries.  Moticakes: Ok we ended up having two orders of Moticakes because we ate our first order so fast! Moticakes are like mini pancakes with your choice of sweet or savory toppings and they have a TON of topping options. They're a great little snack, or, if you're like me and always need a little something sweet after your meal, a great dessert option. We did an order with marshmallow fluff and chocolate chips and a second set with fresh strawberries and Nutella (sweet tooth!). Both were so fun and good!  Selfiecinno: There's a 0% chance that I spelled that right, but the picture was so cool! The Moti Cafe employee took a photo of my brother (with my dad photobombing in the background, of course).  Vibe/decor: Very cool and trendy decor, definitely modern but welcoming and has a cute feeling. I loved the little messages in the tile when you walk in--keep an eye out!  Staff: OMG they were so nice! Every employee we interacted with was friendly, happy to help and answer questions about the menu, even let me take a boomerang of filling the moticakes pan hahaha  Overall, a great experience! I'll definitely return for a full meal (followed by moticakes for dessert of course!)
